      "content": "Taking a probiotic might help with gut health, but it won't replace the need to complete your antibiotic course. Probiotics can support your gut flora, but they won't eliminate the bacteria causing the infection. Stopping antibiotics early can lead to a resurgence of the infection and contribute to antibiotic resistance. It's best to finish the prescribed course to ensure the infection is fully eradicated. If you're concerned about your gut health, discuss this with your doctor, but don't let it interfere with your antibiotic treatment.",
